import React from 'react'; import { Container, Row, Col, Card, ProgressBar } from 'react-bootstrap'; import './Skills.css'; const Skills = () => { const programmingLanguages = [ { name: 'Python', level: 90, icon: 'fab fa-python', color: '#3776ab' }, { name: 'JavaScript', level: 85, icon: 'fab fa-js-square', color: '#f7df1e' }, { name: 'Java', level: 75, icon: 'fab fa-java', color: '#007396' }, ]; const frameworks = [ { name: 'React.js', level: 85, icon: 'fab fa-react', color: '#61dafb' }, { name: 'HTML/CSS', level: 95, icon: 'fab fa-html5', color: '#e34f26' }, { name: 'Tailwind CSS', level: 80, icon: 'fas fa-wind', color: '#38b2ac' }, { name: 'REST API', level: 80, icon: 'fas fa-cogs', color: '#f05032' }, ]; const csFundamentals = [ 'Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA)', 'Database Management Systems (DBMS)', 'Object-Oriented Programming (OOPS)', 'Operating Systems (OS)', 'Computer Networks (CN)', ]; const libraries = [ 'Scikit-learn', 'Matplotlib', 'Pandas', 'NumPy' ]; const softSkills = [ { name: 'Team-Work', level: 90 }, { name: 'Project Management', level: 85 }, { name: 'Agile-Methodology', level: 88 }, ]; const tools = [ { name: 'Git', icon: 'fab fa-git-alt', description: 'Version Control' }, { name: 'GitHub', icon: 'fab fa-github', description: 'Code hosting' }, ]; return (

Skills & Expertise

Programming Languages

{programmingLanguages.map((skill, index) => (
{skill.name}
{skill.level}%
))}

Frameworks

{frameworks.map((skill, index) => (
{skill.name}
{skill.level}%
))}

CS Fundamentals

{csFundamentals.map((skill, index) => (
{skill}
))}

Libraries

{libraries.map((skill, index) => (
{skill}
))}

Additional Skills

{softSkills.map((skill, index) => (
{skill.name} {skill.level}%
))}

Developer Tools

{tools.map((tool, index) => (
{tool.name}

{tool.description}

))}
); }; export default Skills;
